name: DNC convention 2024
summary: The Democratic National Convention (DNC) for 2024 is currently scheduled to take place in August in Chicago. However, recent developments have raised questions about the timing and proceedings of the convention. Some House Democrats are attempting to halt an early effort to nominate Joe Biden before the August convention, while others are planning to hold off on a protest letter until the DNC delays its virtual roll call to nominate Biden. The uncertainty stems from Biden's recent decision to drop out of the presidential race, leaving the party without a clear frontrunner. As a result, the DNC is facing the challenge of finding a suitable replacement candidate and navigating the complexities of the nominating process. The convention is expected to provide further clarity on these matters in the coming months.
